<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="370" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1764½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">20 May, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: It is very interesting
                            indeed that this course of action<note n="76" xml:id="d370fn1">The
                                reference is probably to the proposal to warn American citizens
                                against traveling on armed merchant ships. See <ref target="#pg_404">pp. 404</ref>–<ref target="#pg_406">406</ref>.</note> should
                            have occurred to Mr. Johnson quite independently of any knowledge that
                            it should have been in our minds as among the possibilities.</p>
                        <p>I think, however as I did the other day, that this is at any rate not
                            just the right moment to take such action, even if we have the legal
                            right to take it.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>